dia, or interact with any X     |                    |\n|           |                                     | API v2 endpoint.                              |                    |\n| ✓ ready   | 📦 browser                          | Automate web browser interactions using       | openclaw-workspace |\n|           |                                     | natural language via CLI commands. Use when   |                    |\n|           |                                     | the user asks to browse websites, navigate    |                    |\n|           |                                     | web pages, extract data from websites, take   |                    |\n|           |                                     | screenshots, fill forms, click buttons, or    |                    |\n|           |                                     | interact with web applications.               |                    |\n| ✓ ready   | 📦 cron-mastery                     | Master OpenClaw's timing systems. Use for     | openclaw-workspace |\n|           |                                     | scheduling reliable reminders, setting up     |                    |\n|           |                                     | periodic maintenance (janitor jobs), and      |                    |\n|           |                                     | understanding when to use Cron vs Heartbeat   |                    |\n|           |                                     | for time-sensitive tasks.                     |                    |\n| ✓ ready   | 📦 desktop-control                  | Control desktop applications on Windows —     | openclaw-workspace |\n|           |                                     | launch, close, focus, resize, move windows,   |                    |\n|           |                                     | simulate keyboard/mouse input, manage         |                    |\n|           |                                     | processes, control VSCode, read clipboard,    |                  